<br>
There is still a lot of &quot;basic&quot; physics we need to understand.  The progress in the last five years alone has been astounding, however.  I worked on a fusion experiment at the University of Wisconsin for the better part of a year and there is much steady progress in the field.  Perhaps I may be too optimistic, but everything seems to point to the technology working.<br>
<br>
200 million dollars is nothing.  The experiment I worked on (a small one) cost the government about 5 million to set up.  Both nuclear fission spacecrafts and fusion technologies need to be investigated heavily in my opinion.  We spend billions on maintaining a stockpile of nuclear weapons which could wipe out the world four times over.  Now, I'm not saying we should get rid of all of them, but I'm not sure about the wisdom of maintaining a stock of far more than we could ever need.  That Plutonium could go to much better uses that decaying in warheads. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=contraconstantius>contraconstantius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 10:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bush Wants Fusion by 2037...</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately, fusion technology isn't enough for a fusion reactor. Even if the tech is ready in a year the greenies won't sit back and allow a fusion reactor to be built. Also the polititions have finall say about whether a comercial reactor is built. The best place to build a working fusion reactor might ge the moon, ceres, or somewhere else the ape in charge can't prohibit it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/11/03 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=8>Reply</a